## Ingredients

### For the Crispy Tofu

- [ ] 14 oz Extra-Firm Tofu, pressed and cubed
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Cornstarch
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Neutral Oil
- [ ] 2 Shallots, thinly sliced
- [ ] 3 cloves Garlic, minced
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Soy Sauce or Tamari
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Rice Vinegar
- [ ] 1 tsp Sesame Oil
- [ ] 1 tsp Brown Sugar

### For the Red Cabbage and Mushrooms

- [ ] 2 Tbsp Neutral Oil
- [ ] 8 oz Oyster Mushrooms, torn into strips
- [ ] 1/2 head Red Cabbage, thinly sliced (about 4-5 cups)
- [ ] 2 Shallots, thinly sliced
- [ ] 2 cloves Garlic, minced
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Soy Sauce
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Rice Vinegar
- [ ] 1 tsp Ginger, grated
- [ ] 1/4 tsp Black Pepper

### For the Bowl

- [ ] 8 oz Rice Vermicelli Noodles
- [ ] 1 Cucumber, julienned or thinly sliced
- [ ] 1 large Carrot, julienned or grated
- [ ] 1/4 cup Fresh Cilantro, chopped
- [ ] 1/4 cup Fresh Mint, chopped
- [ ] 2 Green Onions, thinly sliced
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Roasted Peanuts, crushed
- [ ] Lime wedges for serving

### For the Sauce

- [ ] 3 Tbsp Soy Sauce
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Lime Juice
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Water
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Brown Sugar or Maple Syrup
- [ ] 1 clove Garlic, minced
- [ ] 1 tsp Sriracha or Chili Garlic Sauce (optional)

## Recipe

1. Soak rice vermicelli noodles in hot water for 8-10 minutes until softened, then drain and rinse with cold water
1. Pat tofu dry and toss with cornstarch until evenly coated
1. Heat 2 Tbsp oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat
1. Add tofu and cook 3-4 minutes per side until crispy and golden. Transfer to a plate
1. In the same skillet, add 2 Tbsp oil and sliced shallots. Cook 2-3 minutes until softened
1. Add garlic and cook 30 seconds until fragrant
1. Add oyster mushrooms and cook 4-5 minutes until browned and tender
1. Add sliced red cabbage, ginger, and black pepper. Stir-fry for 5-7 minutes until cabbage is softened but still has some crunch
1. Add soy sauce and rice vinegar to the vegetables, stir well, and cook 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat
1. Whisk together all sauce ingredients in a small bowl
1. Assemble bowls with vermicelli noodles as the base
1. Top with saut√©ed red cabbage and mushrooms, crispy tofu, cucumber, carrot, and fresh herbs
1. Drizzle with sauce, sprinkle with crushed peanuts and green onions
1. Serve with lime wedges

## Notes

- Press tofu for at least 15 minutes before cooking for best crispiness
- Tear oyster mushrooms into strips along their natural grain for better texture
- Can substitute shiitake or button mushrooms if oyster mushrooms are unavailable
- Make components ahead and assemble bowls when ready to serve
- For extra protein, add a fried or soft-boiled egg on top
- The red cabbage will turn a beautiful purple color as it cooks
